<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1086,766,1052]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230">
C o m m e n t: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[360,550,766,788]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Porocallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wrasei">
<emphasis box="[360,550,766,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230">Porocallus wrasei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described based on a male and a female from a locality in the Gaoligong Shan, western Yunnan, and subsequently recorded from additional localities in Yunnan southeastwards to the Dawei Shan near Pingbian, close to the border with 
<collectingCountry box="[564,651,854,876]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[671,814,854,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230" pagination="1011 - 1016" refId="ref2085" refString="ASSING V. (2012): A revision of Porocallus SHARP. III. A new species from China and an additional record (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 44 (2): 1011 - 1016." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[830,897,854,876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230" pagination="257 - 262" refId="ref2130" refString="ASSING V. (2015 a): A revision of Porocallus SHARP. IV. A new species from China and additional records (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 47 (1): 257 - 262." type="journal article" year="2015">2015a</bibRefCitation>
). The remarkable intraspecific variation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[436,532,884,905]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Porocallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wrasei">
<emphasis box="[436,532,884,905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230">P. wrasei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was already addressed in 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[802,967,883,905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230" pagination="257 - 262" refId="ref2130" refString="ASSING V. (2015 a): A revision of Porocallus SHARP. IV. A new species from China and additional records (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 47 (1): 257 - 262." type="journal article" year="2015">ASSING (2015a)</bibRefCitation>
. The above specimens are distinguished from all other specimens seen thus far by darker coloration (body practically completely black, except for the narrowly yellowish posterior margin of the elytra and the dark-reddish antennomere XI). The median lobe of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[186,251,1000,1023]" captionStart="Figs 1-9" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1082,212,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-1@2.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-9: Porocallus vietnamensis nov.sp. (1-7) and P. wrasei from Vietnam (8-9): forebody (1); antenna (2); median dorsal portion of head (3); median portion of pronotum (4); median portion of left elytron (5); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (6-8); spermatheca (9). Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 6-9: 0.5 mm; 3-5: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5415888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5415888/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and the spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[505,571,1000,1023]" captionStart="Figs 1-9" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1082,212,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-1@2.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-9: Porocallus vietnamensis nov.sp. (1-7) and P. wrasei from Vietnam (8-9): forebody (1); antenna (2); median dorsal portion of head (3); median portion of pronotum (4); median portion of left elytron (5); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (6-8); spermatheca (9). Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 6-9: 0.5 mm; 3-5: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5415888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5415888/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1230">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), however, are within the range of intraspecific variation.
</paragraph>
